about.summary: py.test plugin that allows you to add environment variables.

name: pytest-env
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pytest-env" %}
{% set version = "0.6.2" %}
{% set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{% set hash_value = "7e94956aef7f2764f3c147d216ce066bf6c42948bb9e293169b1b1c880a580c2" %}

package:
  name: '{{ name|lower }}'
  version: '{{ version }}'

source:
  fn: '{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz'
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  '{{ hash_type }}': '{{ hash_value }}'

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install  --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt
  noarch: python

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - pytest >=2.6.0

test:
  imports:
    - pytest_env
  commands:
    - pytest --help

about:
  home: https://github.com/MobileDynasty/pytest-env
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  # license file is missing from sdist: https://github.com/MobileDynasty/pytest-env/issues/6
  summary: py.test plugin that allows you to add environment variables.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - nicoddemus
